b. Biennial Matching Activity Report 

(See 5 U.S.C. 552a(u)(3)(D)). At the end of each calendar year, the Data Integrity Board of each agency that has participated
in matches covered by the computer matching provisions of the Privacy Act will collect data summarizing that year's
matching activity. The Act requires that such activity be reported every two years. OMB will establish the exact format
of the report, but agencies' Data Integrity Boards should be prepared to report the data identified below both to the
agency head and to OMB.

(1) A listing of the names and positions of the members of the Data Integrity Board and showing separately the name of
